    "updated_at": "2017-03-24T04:09:25Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Since @GraionDilach hinted on an actor definition on the world, it might be worthwhile to check what kinds of actors is populated by ActorsInWorld. Probably the world itself is not included, but my guess is that solving PlayerActor may just divert the issue to some other WeirdActor.\r\n\r\nThen we can consider what solution to take (especially if we discover more things in there). This could be resolved in the Lua script through checking of case scenarios, so this can be delegated to the responsibility of the Lua scripter. But at the least this should be documented.\r\n\r\nFor most scenarios, Using Map.ActorsInBox(_insert code for full map_) in place of Map.ActorsInWorld will resolve this issue, unless you intend to access actors outside the field)\r\n"
  },
